Saudi Arabia]] ([[Basic_Law_of_Saudi_Arabia#History|1992]]) (however, the Basic Law declares the [[Qur'an]] to be the Constitution of Saudi Arabia)\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Constitution of the United Kingdom]] ([[Magna Carta|1215]])\n\n== Constitutions of former countries ==\n*[[Constitution of the Kingdom of Hawai'i (1852)]]\n*[[Catalan Constitutions]]\n*[[Confederate States Constitution]]\n*[[Constitution of Czechoslovakia]]\n*[[Constitution of the Irish Free State]]\n*[[Constitution of Massachusetts]]\n*[[Constitution of May 3, 1791|Constitution of Poland-Lithuania]] (1791)\n*[[Constitution of the Kingdom of Poland]]\n*[[Sretenje Constitution|Constitution of the Principality of Serbia (1835)]]\n*[[Constitution of Prussia (1848)]]\n*[[Constitution of Prussia (1850)]]\n*[[Constitution of Prussia (1920)]]\n*[[Russian Constitution of 1906|Constitution of the Russian Empire]]\n*[[Constitution of the Republic of Texas]]\n*[[Constitution of the Soviet Union]]\n*[[Constitution of Vermont (1777)|Constitution of Vermont Republic]] (1777)\n*[[Constitution of Yugoslavia]]\n**[[Constitutional Charter of Serbia and Montenegro]]\n*[[Corsican Constitution]]\n*[[Constitution of Iran (1907)]]\n*[[Constitution of East Germany|East German constitutions]]\n*[[Ottoman constitution of 1876]]\n*[[Weimar Constitution]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Constitution Day]]\n* [[Constitutional documents]]\n* [[Constitutional law]]\n* [[State constitution (United States)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Wikisource portal|Constitutional documents}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n<!--Categories-->\n[[Category:Constitutions| List]]\n[[Category:Lists of countries|Constitutions]]\n", "name_user": "Ehrenkater", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCodified constitutions (most recent, in use today)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_national_constitutions"}
{"title_page": "Paddraccio", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=July 2010}}\n[[File:Paddraccio.jpg|thumb|270px|Paddraccio]]\n'''Paddraccio''' is a cheese characteristic of [[Rotonda, Basilicata|Rotonda]], [[Basilicata]] in southern [[Italy]].\n\n==Production==\nThe cheese is produced between April and July.   [[Raw milk]] is heated to {{convert|37|-|38|C}} degrees before the (sheep or goat) [[rennet]] is added.   The cheese sets in 20&ndash;30 minutes. When the [[Curd|curds]] breaks, the cheese is transferred to a [[wicker]] container and worked with the fingers. It is then pressed, using the flat of the hand, to end up with a spherical shape. Finally, this fresh cheese with no added salt needing no [[Cheese ripening|ripening]] time is wrapped in fern leaves.\n\n==History==\nIn the past the cheese was used by [[shepherds]] to repay such services as the writing of a letter and in other exchanges of goods or services.\n\nDuring [[Ascension Day]] young priests would call on farmers to ask for milk in order to prepare the local dish ''laganeddre'' and on those days farmers, in order to have the milk available to give, avoided making their own cheese.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cheeses]]\n*[[List of Italian cheeses]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Italian cheeses}}\n\n[[Category:Italian cheeses]]\n[[Category:Sheep's-milk cheeses]]\n[[Category:Cuisine of Basilicata]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=July 2010}}\n[[File:Paddraccio.jpg|thumb|270px|Paddraccio]]\n'''Paddraccio''' is a cheese characteristic of [[Rotonda, Basilicata|Rotonda]], [[Basilicata]] in southern [[Italy]].\n\n==Production==\nThe cheese is produced between April and July.   Raw milk is heated to {{convert|37|-|38|C}} degrees before the (sheep or goat) [[rennet]] is added.   The cheese sets in 20&ndash;30 minutes. When the [[Curd|curds]] breaks, the cheese is transferred to a [[wicker]] container and worked with the fingers. It is then pressed, using the flat of the hand, to end up with a spherical shape. Finally, this fresh cheese with no added salt needing no ripening time is wrapped in fern leaves.\n\n==History==\nIn the past the cheese was used by [[shepherds]] to repay such services as the writing of a letter and in other exchanges of goods or services.\n\nDuring [[Ascension Day]] young priests would call on farmers to ask for milk in order to prepare the local dish ''laganeddre'' and on those days farmers, in order to have the milk available to give, avoided making their own cheese.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cheeses]]\n*[[List of Italian cheeses]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Italian cheeses}}\n\n[[Category:Italian cheeses]]\n[[Category:Sheep's-milk cheeses]]\n[[Category:Cuisine of Basilicata]]\n", "name_user": "Mezze stagioni", "label": "safe", "comment": "wikilink", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paddraccio"}
